article.description: Michael Carey scored 12 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Wagner beat American 55-48 on Sunday for the Seahawks' fourth straight victory.
article.headline: Carey leads Wagner over American 55-48
article.story: NEW YORK -- Michael Carey scored 12 points and grabbed 11 rebounds and Wagner beat American 55-48 on Sunday for the Seahawks' fourth straight victory. James Reed's 3-pointer gave American its first since lead since early on, 40-39, with 6:57 to go. Delante Jones added a basket but Wagner scored the next 10 points, including four each by Carey and Corey Henson to lead 49-42 with 27 seconds left. Charlie Jones and James Washington made 3-pointers for American in the final 24 seconds but Wagner made eight free throws, four by Carey. All four of victories for the Seahawks (4-2) have come at home. Henson scored 14 points for Wagner and Dwaun Anderson added 11. It was Anderson's sixth consecutive double-figure game. Delante Jones scored 20 points, a career high for the freshman. The Eagles (2-6) committed 21 turnovers, which Wagner turned into 23 points.
